Reasoning: The paper discusses object classification, detection, and semantic segmentation using deep neural network-based algorithms, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV). The applications mentioned, such as autonomous driving and robot navigation, fall under robotics (cs.RO). The use of supervised learning and large labeled datasets suggests machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the challenges related to data representation and distribution suggest graphics (cs.GR) as a possible sub-category.
